cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI

The paper proposes a new model for correlated topic modeling that focuses on efficient inference and scalability. The paper's focus on learning compact topic embeddings and capturing topic correlations through the closeness between topic vectors suggests that it falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's application in document classification and retrieval suggests that it could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper's use of variational inference and fast samplers suggests that it could also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
